# Root Docker build context contract for Cloud Run workers.
#
# The worker deploy scripts run `docker build ... -f services/<worker>/Dockerfile .`
# from the repo root, so Docker only reads ignore rules from THIS file. The
# service-local `.dockerignore` files are useful as reference, but they do not
# reduce the root build context by themselves.
#
# Keep this file conservative: exclude generated/local/operational clutter that
# no current worker needs, but do not prune `src/` subtrees aggressively here
# because worker transitive imports can evolve over time.

# VCS / CI / local tooling
.git/
.github/
.vscode/
.idea/
.auth/
.claude/
.codex/
.vercel/
*.swp

# Local build outputs / caches
.next/
.next-local/
.next-build-dir
.next-build-meta.json
out/
dist/
build/
coverage/
blob-report/
playwright-report/
test-results/
artifacts/
.tmp/
*.tsbuildinfo

# Dependencies are installed inside the image
node_modules/

# Local env / secrets
.env*
!.env.example
!.env.local.example

# Repo areas not needed by current Cloud Run worker images
bigquery/
data/
demo-configs/
docs/
full-version/
# public/ is excluded from the worker build context EXCEPT public/branding/,
# which the ops-worker carries into its runtime image for PDF rendering
# (payroll receipts, contractor/finiquito/finance PDFs resolve
# process.cwd()/public/branding/*). Dir-level exception → any future brand
# asset under public/branding/ is included automatically. Mirror of the
# .gcloudignore exception (both ignore files filter the Cloud Build context).
public/*
!public/branding/
!public/branding/**
spec/
tests/

# Test sources
**/*.test.ts
**/*.test.tsx
**/*.spec.ts
src/test/

# Misc
*.tmp
*.log
.DS_Store
